                            <comment id="17914118" author="smiklosovic" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 14:02:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt; it would be nice if you checked what are the differences / additions in doc/cql3/CQL.textile and add it there. CQL.textile is of version 3.4.8 and the document you work on 3.4.3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914122" author="bschoeni" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 14:09:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smiklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smiklosovic&quot;&gt;smiklosovic&lt;/a&gt; Yes, I realize the content needs a lot of love also.  This PR is designed to address just formatting issues with almost no content changes.  Content changes should be in a separate PR.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These formatting changes are +884 &#8722;737 which is fairly substantial.  Content changes mixed in would be hard to review properly as part of this large change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914154" author="michaelsembwever" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 15:39:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is off-topic, but I am also curious a) how we are ensuring CQL.textile and cql_singlefile.adoc are kept in-sync, and b) our thoughts or any past-discussions on automating one off the other&#8230;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914157" author="smiklosovic" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 15:45:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why do we even need to have two? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914162" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 16:00:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As we learned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17709&quot; title=&quot;CQL.textile needs to be made current&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17709&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-17709&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we generate the CQL doc we ship (at least in Debian) from that textile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914175" author="michaelsembwever" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 16:39:56 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the prompt &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We generate a html version from `ant generate-cql-html`&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should include the generated html file into the antora docs, instead of having to maintain the alternative source file in asciidoc format.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are doing something similar in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19915&quot; title=&quot;Enhance the Native Protocols page by replacing the plain text with an interactive, section-based navigation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19915&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19915&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the native protocol spec pages.&lt;br/&gt;
See &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3714/files&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3714/files&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Generate/copy the html file into `modules/cassandra/assets/attachments/` and then create a near-empty .adoc holder file that includes the html file.  (No need for a script here, as the Makefile can just call generate-cql-html and do location change.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt;, what are your thoughts ?  it seems relatively similar amount of work to do this^ instead&#8230;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914239" author="bschoeni" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 21:08:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt; one file sounds good, I don&apos;t know if it needs to be in the modules directory, it&apos;s almost redundant with the content there. The primary purpose of this file is as an online resource for cqlsh if the local CQL.html wasn&apos;t installed (as it&apos;s not today with &apos;pip install cqlsh&apos;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, since the modules files are in AsciiDoc, it&apos;s a little awkward that this file would be in textile as much of the content overlaps. For example, if you add content to describe new functions to functions.adoc it would be nice to be able to cut-n-paste it to the CQL help file in the same format.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914243" author="michaelsembwever" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 21:42:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For it to be included on the website it needs to be part of the cassandra-builds antora build.  That needs .adoc files.  So we need that holding .adoc file that includes the html file.  Only html files in the `modules/cassandra/assets/attachments/` directory can be included.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19915&quot; title=&quot;Enhance the Native Protocols page by replacing the plain text with an interactive, section-based navigation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19915&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19915&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the holding .adoc file is auto-generated by the script but that&apos;s not needed here.  It would be just a simple  cql_singlefile.adoc something like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
= Cassandra Query Language
:toc:

[source, html]
++++
include::attachment$CQL.html[CQL]
++++
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914738" author="bschoeni" created="Mon, 20 Jan 2025 17:17:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt; but why are the docs in modules in AsciiDoc while CQL.textile uses textile for the same content&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;functions.adoc:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13074168/13074168_screenshot-2.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CQL.textile:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13074167/13074167_screenshot-1.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914770" author="michaelsembwever" created="Mon, 20 Jan 2025 18:52:39 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;but why are the docs in modules in AsciiDoc while CQL.textile uses textile for the same content&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The original is CQL.textile.  This has always been generated as part of the in-tree build and bundled into artefacts/releases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After the antora build was introduced (using asciidoc files), from cassandra-website that builds our website, we duplicated the file to cql_singlefile.adoc so it was also on the website.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We didn&apos;t spent the time back then to figure out how to just use the CQL.textile source.  (And we don&apos;t yet have in place any way to build the whole antora in-tree module into html that can be bundled into releases, but we eventually want that too, ref: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17260&quot; title=&quot;Antora site.yml in-tree so in-tree html can be generated (again)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17260&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-17260&lt;/a&gt; )&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916123" author="bschoeni" created="Wed, 22 Jan 2025 17:24:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve chatted directly with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt; because I didn&apos;t understand all the moving parts here with anatora, textile and asciidoc.&#160; Based upon that, I suggest the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a) Review and merge this AsciiDoc syntax fixes (PR 3803) for cql_singefille.adoc with it&apos;s 800+ line changes.&#160; This is a markup only change, but its corrects really terrible miss-formatting on our website which is the URL CQLSH brings up for help. It&apos;s a pre-requisite for fixing the content.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b) Creating a new Jira to sync content between cql_singlefile.adoc and CQL.textile with the aim of switching to AsciiDoc (.adoc) going forward.&#160; This addresses &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smiklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smiklosovic&quot;&gt;smiklosovic&lt;/a&gt; notes that the content between the files is inconsistent (3.4.8 vs 3.4.3 among others).&#160; I&apos;ll work on this next.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c) Fixing the doc build to generate HTML from AsciiDoc for inclusion in the build and which is referenced locally by cqlsh with a tarball install. This is part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17260&quot; title=&quot;Antora site.yml in-tree so in-tree html can be generated (again)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17260&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-17260&lt;/a&gt;.&#160; This will use asciidoctorj, which is the same tooling as anatora.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Today we have 212 files in .adoc format and just one in Textile (CQL.textile) on &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/apache/cassandra&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;github.com/apache/cassandra&lt;/a&gt;. Also,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;AsciiDoc has been contributed to the Eclipse Foundation and now managed by them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Eclipse AsciiDoc Working Group is drafting a standard&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://asciidoc-wg.eclipse.org/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://asciidoc-wg.eclipse.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;IntelliJ has plugin support for AsciiDoc and renders it beautifully in the IDE &#8211; which I used for my PR to verify correctness&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;AsciiDoc has support for many source highlighters, with Highlights.js working with asciidoctorj&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Attached is the new cql_singlefile.html generated by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;asciidoctorj -a source-highlighter=highlight.js -a highlightjs-theme=vs cassandra/pages/developing/cql/cql_singlefile.adoc&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13074197/13074197_cql_singlefile.html&quot; title=&quot;cql_singlefile.html attached to CASSANDRA-20195&quot;&gt;cql_singlefile.html&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916126" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 22 Jan 2025 17:35:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do we need 2)?  Can we instead throw textile away once we have 3)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916154" author="michaelsembwever" created="Wed, 22 Jan 2025 18:19:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(2) is just about bringing over the latest stuff only in CQL.textile, into cql_singlefile.adoc&lt;br/&gt;
Yes, (3) means throwing away CQL.textile.  (`ant gen-doc` would make the asciidoctorj invocation, instead of the textile generation. 17260 is really a fourth step, where asciidoctorj would no longer be needed &#8211; instead we can generate a dynamic in-tree antora project, and all in-tree adocs are bundled as html into release artefacts.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m for the approach &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt;, thanks for writing it up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916164" author="bschoeni" created="Wed, 22 Jan 2025 19:23:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; yes, that&apos;s the idea, to replace the sole textile file (with AsciiDoc) once we can build it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916407" author="bschoeni" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2025 13:33:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=smiklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;smiklosovic&quot;&gt;smiklosovic&lt;/a&gt;&#160; if one of you could review the PR that would be terrifice.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916410" author="smiklosovic" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2025 13:45:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will delegate this to other people. Honestly, I lost track of what is going on here &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916527" author="michaelsembwever" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2025 21:15:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bschoeni&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bschoeni&quot;&gt;bschoeni&lt;/a&gt;, can we get the same patch for 4.0, 4.1 and 5.0 please &#128591;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916846" author="bschoeni" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2025 20:53:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt; 5.0, yes, it&apos;s simple, PR for 5.0 added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 4.0 and 4.1 files have 100+ lines of differences, and different from each-other.&#160; it doesn&apos;t seem worth the effort to manually reapply 800 lines of changes. I think cql_singlefile is used only by CQLSH when the local CQL.html wasn&apos;t install &#8211; this is the case if you &apos;pip install cqlsh&apos; which doesn&apos;t bundle CQL.html.&#160; But the pypl.org version latest is 5.0, so the relevance of this for 4.0/4.1 seems minor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916911" author="michaelsembwever" created="Sat, 25 Jan 2025 10:19:31 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The 4.0 and 4.1 files have 100+ lines of differences, and different from each-other.  it doesn&apos;t seem worth the effort&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;agree&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17916917" author="michaelsembwever" created="Sat, 25 Jan 2025 11:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/2a623b6cf3a3923ac64b0542c06d8b518a09b8cb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/2a623b6cf3a3923ac64b0542c06d8b518a09b8cb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
